race.comment: GET HONOR (8) was met with market support on debut at Sandown Hillside and justified it nicely with a tough win, coming from off the pace and proving too strong late to score by half a length. She's a well bred sort who can improve up in trip in what looks a winnable race. ROSE OF SHALAA (5) is going okay without winning this time in, close up in a bunched finish at Geelong in this grade last start. Each way. QUEEN BEIRA (6) put in a better effort at Cranbourne last time and could surprise at odds with a good map. POWER CABLE (2) is mixing her form this time in but the pieces are there to say she's up to winning this if she gets the right run.
